    "Each convolutional layer in GCN is capable of processing information from the first-order neighborhood, thereby capturing vertex details from immediate neighbors.",
    "Through the stacking of multiple convolutional layers, GCN aggregates information from multiple-order neighborhoods to derive embedding representations for all vertices.",
    "The fundamental concept behind graph convolutional neural networks is to amalgamate information from a node's own attributes and its neighboring nodes, with a focus on the connectivity between two nodes.",
    "This approach enables a more comprehensive understanding of each node, taking into account the structural information embedded in the data.However, due to the issue of gradient vanishing in traditional GCN networks [30], we introduce residual graph convolutional networks in this section to learn node embeddings.",
